Self Portrait, 2023
____________________
A teacher in art school years ago challenged me to do at least one self portrait a year for the rest of my life, and it’s a challenge I’ve taken to heart. I try to time them to be the first art I make in the new year. Swipe to see a sampling of 12 years worth of self portraits. It’s interesting to see how I’ve evolved physically, and also to see how the mediums have shifted (oil paint to marker to colored pencil to now drawing digitally on an iPad).

🐐 Capricorn ♑️

🌊 Aquarius ♒️ 
_______________
The Aquarius entry to the zodiac series I’ve been working on. Some details - the figure as the water bearer; orchids, represented here as a tattoo; a necklace of aquamarine; and a color palette of blues, teals and soft pinks.

“The Queens, named to commemorate the glorious past reign of the women, are also friends of the faggots. The men hate the queens and try in every way to exterminate them. The queens are not, however, afraid. They laugh at the men and taunt them for being so stupid and coarse. Sometimes the faggots join the queens to laugh at the men and tell them they are stupid and coarse. Usually the faggots sit and listen while the queens tell of their thrilling adventures and applaud when the queens, once again, escape from the clumsy clutches of the men.” - excerpt from “The Faggots and their Friends Between Revolutions” by Larry Mitchell
____________
I revisit this book often, it’s a favorite of mine. Though first published in 1977 I find it still resonates with events we are currently experiencing collectively. This passage came to mind for me with this current rise of conservative bullshit aimed at denigrating Trans people and Drag performers. They love to use hate and fear tactics to deflect from their political failings and harmful ideologies, and sadly it’s a strategy that proves effective time and time again in this country. So please, stand up for Trans people. Stand up for Drag performers. And call out this bullshit, shut it down. Have uncomfortable conversations with people around you who may be ignorant about these topics. This isn’t just some “culture war”, this is hateful rhetoric that is fast turning into hateful legislation negatively impacting the lives of real humans just trying to live their lives authentically. We need you to step up, especially straight cis allies.
Re-sharing this drawing I did two years ago, as the message feels more timely than ever. #protecttranslives 💙💗🤍

🐟 Pisces ♓️
_______________
The Pisces entry of my zodiac series. Some details - a seascape backdrop, the symbol of the two fish, the lotus flower (here as a tattoo on the figure); a necklace of amethyst stones and a color palette of purples, turquoise and soft blues.

Self Portrait
________________
Though I did one recently, I felt like doing a less stylized self portrait as a way to work through some emotional upheaval I’ve been processing the past few months.  On a micro level - it’s been your basic “but what am I doing with my life?! Am I a big failure?!” existential crisis, coupled with the financial uncertainties/anxieties of trying to be a working artist, and then periods of deep depression that inevitably follow all the anxiety spirals. On a macro level - trying to make sense of this increasingly dystopian timeline we find ourselves in. How do we engage with this reality as our best selves, and help others through it? How do we avoid sliding into fear and hopelessness? 
_____________
A teacher challenged me years ago to do self portraits often, especially during periods of personal transformation/intense emotion. So I took her at her word, and wanted to document these big feelings I’m having. Lots of heavy questions were surely not answered through this exercise, but it was a bit of a cathartic release for me nevertheless.

🔥Aries ♈️ 
_______________
Some fiery energy for the Aries entry of the my zodiac series. Was aiming to capture a playful, mischievous, outgoing and energetic vibe…all characteristics attributed to Aries. I sort of based the figure after the character of Puck from Shakespeare’s “A Midsummer Night’s Dream”. Some details associated with Aries - the symbol of the ram horns, a bloodstone necklace, the thistle (here as a tattoo), honeysuckle flowers, and a warmer color palette including reds and oranges.
Tender Moments 💜

Hadn’t drawn from life in ages, or worked with non-digital mediums in years so it was nice to dust off that skill set. These are all colored pencil, poses ranging from 10-20 min…it’s honestly good for me to have a time constraint sometimes, because usually when left to my own devices I tinker on the same drawing for HOURS (sometimes even days and weeks 🙃)

🌸 Taurus ♉️
_______________
Was going for an overall theme of “grounded comfort, security and sensuality” for Taurus. Some details associated with Taurus - the symbol of the bull horns; an emerald necklace; LOTS of florals are connected to Taurus, I’m guessing because seasonally it’s the height of spring…we’ve got foxglove, roses and peonies around the figure, and poppies (represented here as a tattoo). Lastly, a color palette of soft greens, pinks and earthy tones.

Mullet Moment 💇🏻‍♀️

Many thanks to Greg @gregcassese for this amazing cut, and for being such a lovely safe space for this big summer hair refresh 🖤
______________

Some thoughts - 

- You hold a lot in your hair. It’s been an intense couple of years both collectively and personally. That’s a lot of heavy energy to be carrying around. I was ready for a fresh start and to let go of that dead weight. 

- I deeply appreciate the lovely response my long hair generated, and as a result had been scared to cut it for fear of what others would think/say. Trying to calm those anxieties and just do what makes me happy. 

- Experimenting with hair has been incredibly affirming. When I first dyed and then grew it, it ignited a shift in myself and in turn how I interact with the world around me. It sounds dramatic, but hair really can be that powerful. It’s a joy to play with different looks, and l’ve been itching for a big change. 

- I’m gonna keep this for a bit, but when I’m ready to go long again I look forward to the grow out. Last time I was so impatiently focused on the end goal of long hair that I didn’t fully appreciate the process. This time I’d like to be more chill and playful about it, even through the inevitable awkward phases.

- I’m donating the hair I’ve cut off. It’s something I’ve always wanted to do. My long hair brought me joy, and I’m happy to pay it forward 🥰

Art Swap with my lovely and very talented friend Luis @shmoonify (here is mine of him, swipe through to see his beautiful drawing of me). 💚

There are lots of downsides to this platform, but the biggest positive that keeps me active on here is connecting with other queer artists all over the world. Though we’ve never met in person, Luis and I have been friends on here for maybe 6-7 years now? We chat almost daily about everything from art to boys, and he’s someone I admire and appreciate very much. 

Over the years we’ve done a few art swaps, and it’s been cool to see how both our art styles and appearances have evolved. It just worked out that we both debuted dramatic hair changes recently, so the time felt right for another art exchange 💖
Some daddies bein cute 🥹🖤

🩵 Gemini Season ♊️
_______________

Some details associated with Gemini - the symbol of the twins; a purple agate necklace and pearl earrings on the figures; florals- a field of lavender and Lily of the Valley (here represented as a tattoo on the right side figure, a personal favorite flower of mine). Lastly, a color palette involving lots of teals, cyan and purples. 

People have asked, they’re not intended to be me…I invented characters for this series but I do need a human body to reference so I end up modeling the poses (my phone is full of me acting out random poses for drawing references 🤣). Some of me inevitably gets in there despite trying my best to avoid that. 

This drawing is the final entry in my zodiac series that I’ve been working on for over a year! A really fun project, learned a lot about the symbolism and attributes of each sign. Definitely may revisit this series again at some point 💜

Re-sharing this drawing I did a few years ago as a tribute to the 49 victims of the shooting at Pulse Nightclub in Orlando, FL, which took place 7 years ago today. I’ve drawn 49 flowers in Pride colors to celebrate them. 

Senseless shootings like this are becoming more and more frequent in this country, as is a rise in hateful legislation, rhetoric and violence towards the Queer community. It’s infuriating, and frightening. Please, please be safe this Pride season. I hope we can continue to celebrate, uplift and protect one another through these trying times. 

❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🤎🖤

Rest in Power, O’Shea Sibley 🤍
____________________

I can’t stop think about this awful story; I wanted to create a tribute to O’Shea, who was killed in an act of hate fueled violence last week for dancing with his friends while being visibly, joyfully Queer. It is an indictment on a profoundly sick society that breeds this kind of hatred for anyone who is different, for anyone who strays from the path of stifling gender norms and heteronormativity. That visible Queer Joy is so frightening to a status quo of extremely fragile masculinity, that the vibrant light of Queer creative expression immediately needs to be violently extinguished to maintain that status quo.

We live in such a culture of normalized violence in this country, where the most marginalized communities (especially Black Queer and Trans people) are continuously dehumanized through hateful rhetoric that leads directly to senseless violence like this. My heart hurts for all those who personally knew O’Shea, and the wider collective loss at his passing. I hope his memory can be an inspiration to not give into fear and despair (because that is what they want us to do) but to shine in our Queerness, to keep dancing and to look out for and uplift one another. #osheasibley

Proud of this birthday self portrait, and wanted to share an in process reel for it. It’s condensed to 30 seconds but it’s many hours of work spread out over the course of a few days. I was an oil painter for years before switching to illustration; drawing in Procreate on an iPad allows me to combine elements of both into my process. It starts as a very rough sketch and I then work many layers of detailing over it until it starts to take shape ✍🏻💜💫

“The Kiss of Death” inspired by a sculpture of the same name located in Poblenou Cemetery in Barcelona, Spain. It is an example of a “momento mori”, an artistic trope with roots in the medieval period and beyond portraying death as a winged skeleton bestowing a kiss on a young man. Getting into spooky season vibes by way of my nerdy art history interests ☠️

Wanted to take a minute to thank everyone who stopped by the opening of Bliss: A Queer Exhibition the other night. It was a really special evening that I’m honestly still processing. A humbling honor to share space with such talented artists and such a joy organizing and co-curating this show with @zachgrear and @kitschharris. Thank you @ericmsosa for inviting us to put this show together in the gallery space at @cmoneverybodybk 💜

The show features the work of 28 incredibly talented local queer artists. If you’re looking for original queer art to buy this is a great chance to do so; you’ll be supporting the artists directly as they keep 100% of their profits. Thrilled that a few pieces have already sold! Show is up through January 11, spread the word and bring your friends 💜

✨Golden Hour✨

I created this drawing for Bliss: A Queer Exhibition, the group show currently on view at @cmoneverybodybk curated by @zachgrear @kitschharris and myself. I was aiming to capture that sense of being wrapped in a lover’s arms, getting lost in their eyes, the world melting away to just…bliss. It’s been really lovely to see how each of the 28 artists in this show interpreted the theme of bliss in their own beautiful and unique ways. Show is up through Jan 11, check it out 💜
Thank you all for following along and supporting me and my art this year 💜 #artvsartist2023
